The '''Pingtung Line''' ({{lang|zh-tw|å±æ±ç·}}) is a line of the [[Taiwan Railway Administration]]. It is 61.3&nbsp;km long, of which 20.9&nbsp;km is [[double track]]. <ref>[http://www.railway.gov.tw/en/yearbook/yearbook-4.aspx Taiwan Railways Administration]</ref>

==History==
This railroad was completed in 1941.
It is electrified (25KV) with two tracks from Kaohsiung to Pingtung.
Most trains start or end from Kaohsiung, Pingtung stations.

